1
00:00:00,266 --> 00:00:03,266
oftentimes when I make new patterns for my EBF and vacuum freezers

2
00:00:03,266 --> 00:00:05,933
I get asked why do I make patterns with the hot ingots

3
00:00:06,333 --> 00:00:08,900
now I know how much some of you love ore-dictionary card

4
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:12,100
and what I'm going to say works different in different mod packs

5
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:17,900
the thing is that I don't see any real advantage in making edited patterns that don't show the hot ingots

6
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:18,733
like, yeah

7
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:20,900
you have one less pattern to deal with

8
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:24,000
but the one you have to make is a little bit more complicated

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,300
so my take is that most people do that

10
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:30,033
only because they feel better if they use the ore-dictionary card

11
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:32,700
but if you pattern hot ingots there are some advantages

12
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:37,600
the biggest one is that most of the times you're waiting for EBF while the vacuum freezer has nothing to do

13
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:40,400
but sometimes when you do some specific ingot

14
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,600
EBF will be faster than the vacuum freezer

15
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:45,633
and your vacuum freezer will be stuck cooling things

16
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:46,933
if you pattern hot ingots

17
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:50,033
you can make a dedicated interface with blocking mode for those ingots

18
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:53,900
that way, the ingots that are faster to cool than to melt can pass

19
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,600
in front of those slower ingots

20
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:59,900
and you can keep working on other things while your superconductor slowly cool down

21
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:04,666
another advantage is that you can see from AE2 crafting UI what the issue is

22
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:08,033
here we can guess ingots are waiting to be inserted into the vacuum freezer

23
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:12,433
here we can see a lot of ingots queued up inside the vacuum freezer that are being cooled down

24
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:16,133
while here the issue is the EBF having trouble blasting some tough materials

25
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,800
as you normally expect

26
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:20,133
another reason which I'm not vouching for too much

27
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:23,400
is that you can also fine tune how many ingots are going inside the machines at once

28
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,666
to better use the parallel capacity of each machine

29
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:30,333
another reason is that, in GTNH end game mostly

30
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:34,333
you will probably want to use crafting input buffers and crafting input proxies

31
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:38,100
and unless you want to optionally filter the output of a gorge

32
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:42,266
you most likely want to either redo all of the patterns once you get those

33
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:45,166
or if you do hot ingots patterns early on (?)

34
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:46,733
you already have the patterns done

35
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:50,066
now those were my takes mostly for GTNH

36
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,333
maybe I forgot something

37
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:52,700
maybe it's different in other packs

38
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:53,333
I don't know

39
00:01:53,566 --> 00:01:55,266
I just wanted to put that in a video

40
00:01:55,266 --> 00:01:56,800
so every time someone asks me

41
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,933
I can point them to this video

42
00:01:58,933 --> 00:01:59,466
bye bye

43
00:00:00,266 --> 00:00:03,266
通常当我为我的EBF和真空冰箱制作新图案时

44
00:00:03,266 --> 00:00:05,933
有人问我为什么要用热锭制作图案

45
00:00:06,333 --> 00:00:08,900
现在我知道你们中的一些人有多喜欢词典卡。

46
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:12,100
我要说的在不同的mod包中工作不同

47
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:17,900
问题是，我看不出制作不显示热锭的编辑图案有什么真正的优势。

48
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:18,733
就像，是的

49
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:20,900
你少了一个要处理的模式

50
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:24,000
但是你要做的有点复杂。

51
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,300
所以我的看法是大多数人都这样做

52
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:30,033
那是因为他们用字典卡会感觉好些

53
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:32,700
但是如果你图案热元宝有一些优势

54
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:37,600
最大的一个是，大多数时候你在等待EBF，而真空冰箱却无事可做

55
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:40,400
但有时当你做一些特定的元宝时

56
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,600
EBF会比真空冷冻机快

57
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:45,633
你的真空冰箱会卡在冷却东西上

58
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:46,933
如果你图案热元宝

59
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:50,033
您可以为这些元宝制作具有阻塞模式的专用接口

60
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:53,900
这样冷却速度快于熔化速度的钢锭就可以通过

61
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,600
在那些慢元宝面前

62
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:59,900
当你的超导体慢慢冷却下来时，你可以继续做其他事情

63
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:04,666
另一个优点是您可以从AE2制作UI中看到问题所在

64
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:08,033
在这里，我们可以猜测元宝正在等待插入真空冰箱

65
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:12,433
在这里，我们可以看到许多钢锭在真空冰箱内排队，正在冷却

66
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:16,133
而这里的问题是EBF在爆破一些坚韧的材料时遇到了麻烦

67
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,800
正如您通常期望的那样

68
00:01:17,933 --> 00:01:20,133
另一个我不能保证太多的原因

69
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:23,400
您还可以微调一次进入机器的元宝数量

70
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,666
更好地利用每台机器的并行容量

71
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:30,333
另一个原因是，在GTNH结束游戏大多

72
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:34,333
您可能希望使用制作输入缓冲区和制作输入代理

73
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:38,100
除非你想选择性地过滤峡谷的输出

74
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:42,266
一旦你得到这些，你很可能想重做所有的模式

75
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:45,166
或者如果你早期做热锭图案（？）

76
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:46,733
你已经把图案做好了。

77
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:50,066
这些主要是我对GTNH的看法。

78
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,333
也许我忘了什么

79
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:52,700
也许其他包里不一样

80
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:53,333
我不知道。

81
00:01:53,566 --> 00:01:55,266
我只是想把它放在视频里。

82
00:01:55,266 --> 00:01:56,800
所以每次有人问我

83
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,933
我可以给他们指这段视频

84
00:01:58,933 --> 00:01:59,466
拜拜

